Authentication Flow

User signs up â†’ data saved in MongoDB (password hashed)

User logs in â†’ backend generates JWT token

Token + user name stored in localStorage

ProtectedRoute checks token before accessing dashboard

Dashboard displays Welcome UserName

Logout clears localStorage and redirects to login

